      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a museum-quality example of the E46 chassis. Powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, it features individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS system for razor-sharp throttle response across the 8,000 RPM powerband. This unit features the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential. The subframe has been professionally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been addressed, ensuring structural and mechanical longevity. Finished in impeccable Alpine White with a flawless interior, this vehicle retains its original factory tolerances and performance characteristics.",
